Shock As ANC Ward Councillor Shot And Killed In KZN Published: 31 August 2017 Written by Online Correspondent Share on Facebook View Comments The 34-year-old was gunned down on Wednesday night outside a community hall, where he had attended a meeting. Kwazi Mkhize, the African National Congress (ANC) Ward 3 Councillor of Mkhambathini Municipality, in KwaZulu-Natal, has been shot dead. A terse communique from Mzi Zuma, ANC regional secretary for the Moses Mabhida Region, said Mkhize was gunned down on Wednesday night outside the Nkanyezini Community Hall, where he had attended a meeting. &ldquo;The Ward 3 Councillor was gunned down around 19:30. A life cut short at 34 years of age,&rdquo; said Zuma. &ldquo;We wish to extend our heartfelt condolences to his family, his comrades in the ANC, colleagues in councils, friends and his community that he served with dedication and passion up to the last day.&rdquo; Police could not be immediately reached for comment, but unconfirmed reports suggested that the assailants remain unknown and no arrests have yet been made. View the discussion thread. blog comments powered by DISQUS back to top Google Tweet Pin it Tweet Next